      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "62325341-2d15-476a-b7e8-13ce6140a462",
        "title": "Feature",
        "value": "Aluminum Housing Enhances Cooling and Durability",
        "information": "Features"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "dfb0ba6b-6074-42ba-bb17-d586a4819da2",
        "title": "Silence, Simplified",
        "value": "A computer power supply’s USB bus is often sourced from an inadequately filtered switch -mode power supply, that injects noise into connected equipment leading to data errors, loss, and jitter. Simply insert the iSilencer Max between your computer and DAC to effectively cancel out all incoming noise, leaving you with a cleaner, warmer and more transparent sound.",
        "information": "Product Feature"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "62f44d4a-67fe-4000-95e1-9d09bb26013f",
        "title": "Military Precision",
        "value": "Inspired by military radar cancellation techniques, our proprietary Active Noise Cancellation 3 technology duplicates incoming noise signals from the USB and inverts the polarity, effectively cancelling out incoming electromagnetic and radio interference. This technology means that measured noise drops by 100x (40dB) in comparison to the common noise filter.",
        "information": "Product Feature"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "2ed255cc-8ffd-4829-bdd0-77548cef373f",
        "title": "Maximum Compatibility",
        "value": "The input of the iSilencer Max now supports up to 100W (20V/5A). This greatly expands the list of devices it is compatible with and removes it from the confines of USB DAC Applications.",
        "information": "Product Feature"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "ccbb6d8e-99b5-4594-808c-27797f489bb4",
        "title": "Perfectly Balanced",
        "value": "The REBalance technology inside the iSilencer Max rebalances the USB signal to address DC offset and jitter, leading to distortion, and in turn, data packet errors. This technology cleans up the digital signal and ensures the signal received by the DAC is identical to the original source.",
        "information": "Product Feature"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "290f7bab-c967-4c7b-bb96-ad654ee23d4c",
        "title": "Speed without Compromise",
        "value": "iSilencer Max supports USB 3.0 high-speed data transfer, significantly faster than USB 2.0 standards. This means that it does not impair playback of hi-res audio files, regardless of quality or file size.",
        "information": "Product Feature"
      },
      {
        "_type": "overviewField",
        "_key": "0308d154-cbb9-4f91-a618-7452fad0e5a6",
        "title": "Interference Immune",
        "value": "The aluminum housing of the iSilencer Max is not just for durability. The chassis acts as a heatsink, enhancing cooling performance of the unit. It also ensures complete shielding against Electromagnetic Interference (EMI).",
        "information": "Product Feature"
